The topic of the course is an introduction to ecosemiotics - i.e., the discipline on the border of ecology and cultural semiotics. Its main questions include the interpretation of natural and cultural environment, the mechanisms that create and balance the environmental conflicts. For understanding ecosemiotics the course gives a preview of ecology and the possibilities for applying these in ecosemiotic paradigm are discussed. The course deals also with the history and typology of the relationships between culture and nature.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives a systematic overview of the basics of ecology, ecosemiotic paradigm, and relations between culture and nature. Populations, ecosystems, societies and cultural phenomena are treated as semiotic and communicative webs by emphasizing their structure, dynamics and interrelations. Semiotic aspects of environmental problems are analyzed.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) After completing the course the student is familiar with the basics of ecology and major environmental problems; 2) knows theoretical foundations of ecosemiotics and is able to apply these independently; 3) has an overview of essential authors and directions of environmental thought.
